/* Bluff word data — packed strings, one 5-char word after another.
 * Two pools:
 *   BLUFF_ANSWERS_PACKED — daily-target pool (the canonical NYT-era
 *     Wordle answer list, ~2,300 common words; sourced from
 *     cfreshman/wordle-answers gist).
 *   BLUFF_VALID_PACKED   — full accepted-guess vocabulary (~14,855
 *     words; sourced from tabatkins/wordle-list, MIT). Includes the
 *     answer pool.
 * Packing as one concatenated string is ~3× smaller than a JSON array
 * (no quotes, no commas) and gzips down to ~50 KB on the wire.
 */
window.BLUFF_ANSWERS_PACKED = "";
window.BLUFF_VALID_PACKED = "";
